<title type="html"><![CDATA[Famicom Cartridges == Worse than Oysters]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=536&amp;p=4298#p4298"><![CDATA[
As I understand, most of them simply <em>snap</em> together, and there is a somewhat reliable method for opening them:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">--\*<br />|  \l<br />|t |a<br />|o |b<br />|p |e<br />|  /l<br />--/*</div><br /><br />1. Hold the cartridge so the label is facing the palm of your hand.<br /><br />2. Squeeze the curved edges together (marked *) from the front using your index finger and thumb.<br /><br />3. Pull the cartridge apart.<br /><br />I don't know if this works on all carts, and I haven't tried it myself, but I have seen the method recommended and it apparently works reasonably well.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Tue Sep 06, 2005 8:23 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
