<title type="html"><![CDATA[Famicom Cartridges == Worse than Oysters]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=536&amp;p=4293#p4293"><![CDATA[
Ok, so I've got a number of famicom cartridges with a wide selection of mappers and I want to take them apart.  A few cartridges, like the Koei MMC5 ones have visible, easily removable screws (yay!)  Others seem to have no screws at all (I've already destroyed one set of labels only to find out that there were no screws at all, just molding indentations where you'd expect a screw in the middle, on both sides!).<br /><br />So, my question is: Is there any magic way to open these snap-together famicom carts, short of smashing them with a hammer?<br /><br />--<br />joat<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6">joat</a> — Mon Sep 05, 2005 11:23 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
